quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,88,"And they say, "
  19,89,"You have done an atrocious thing."
  19,90,"The heavens almost rupture therefrom and the earth splits open and the mountains collapse in devastation"
  20,70,"So the magicians fell down in prostration.{1} They said, ",footnotes:1:After they had seen the miracles which Allāh had given Moses and that they were realities and not merely impressions of magic.
  20,71,"[Pharaoh] said, "
  20,72,"They said, ",footnotes:1:This phrase has also been interpreted as an oath, i.e., "...by Him who created us."
  21,46,"And if [as much as] a whiff of the punishment of your Lord should touch them, they would surely say, "
  21,47,"And We place the scales of justice for the Day of Resurrection, so no soul will be treated unjustly at all. And if there is [even] the weight of a mustard seed,{1} We will bring it forth. And sufficient are We as accountant.",footnotes:1:i.e., anything as small or insignificant as a mustard seed.
  21,48,"And We had already given Moses and Aaron the criterion and a light and a reminder{1} for the righteous",footnotes:1:These are three qualities of the Torah.
  22,22,"Every time they want to get out of it [i.e., Hellfire] from anguish, they will be returned to it, and [it will be said], "
  22,23,"Indeed, Allāh will admit those who believe and do righteous deeds to gardens beneath which rivers flow. They will be adorned therein with bracelets of gold and pearl, and their garments therein will be silk."
  22,24,"And they had been guided [in worldly life] to good speech, and they were guided to the path of the Praiseworthy."